## Operator Breakdown

- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: cognitive_level|metaphor_lens — Distinguishes between six discrete Bloom's levels (remember, understand, apply, analyze, evaluate, create) and three thinking metaphors (mechanistic, living systems, journey) as separate but interlocking analytical dimensions
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: learner|framework — Relates individual learner preferences (Kolb's diverging, assimilating, converging, accommodating) to the taxonomic and metaphoric frameworks, mapping personal style to structural affordance
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: lower_order|higher_order — Transforms cognition from lower-order operations (remember, understand) through mid-range (apply, analyze) to higher-order synthesis (evaluate, create), with metaphor shifts catalyzing the transition
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: simple_recall|creative_synthesis — Grows cognitive capacity from rote memory toward creative integration, each Bloom's level building on those below, each metaphor expanding the space of possibility
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: concrete_experience|abstract_conceptualization — Cycles through Kolb's experiential learning loop: concrete experience, reflective observation, abstract conceptualization, active experimentation, grounding the hierarchy in lived practice
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: hierarchy|nested_structure — Structures the entire framework as a 3-level nested hierarchy: Bloom's Taxonomy as the overarching scaffold, thinking metaphors nested within each level, Kolb's learning styles as the innermost layer

## Z-State
:integration — Three established cognitive models (Bloom's, thinking metaphors, Kolb's LSI) are unified into a single operational hierarchy, producing a comprehensive map for understanding how individuals learn, think, and create across multiple dimensions simultaneously

